$ DOM example: document.getElementById

`→ development/web/browser/object-model/document[document].getElementById('xyz')` returns the node in a document whose `id` → development/web/HTML/attributes[attribute] has the value `xyz`.
-
The returned object inherits from `→ development/web/DOM/interfaces-mixins/Element`.

gh|about-Document-Object-Model|/Node/Document/getElementById.html||

sa:

  → development/web/DOM/examples/Node/Document/getElementsByName[`document.getElementsByName('abc')`] returns an array of elements whose `name` attribute is `abc`.

  → development/web/DOM/examples/Node/Document/getElementsByTagName[`document.getElementsByTagName('div')`] returns an array of the → development/web/HTML/tags/div[`<div>`] elements in a HTML document.

  → development/web/DOM/examples[DOM examples]
